    "plan_content": "Here's the implementation plan for `uv cache stats`:\n\n## Summary\n\n**8 files to touch** (2 new, 6 modified):\n\n### New files\n- `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` — the command implementation\n- `crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs` — integration tests\n\n### Modified files\n1. **`crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs`** — add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` preview feature + `\"cache-stats\"` string in `as_str()` and `FromStr`\n2. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` enum + new `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct (identical shape to `SizeArgs`)\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — `mod cache_stats` + `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats`\n4. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — one new match arm dispatching `CacheCommand::Stats` → `commands::cache_stats`\n5. **`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — `cache_stats()` command builder + `with_filtered_cache_stats()` filter\n6. **`crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs`** — `mod cache_stats` under the `test-python,test-pypi` cfg gate\n\n### Key design decisions\n- **`diskus::DiskUsage`** is already a dependency — no Cargo.toml changes needed.\n- **`CacheBucket::Python`** is omitted from `CacheBucket::iter()` (used by prune/clean) but is included explicitly in stats so users see the full picture (all 11 buckets).\n- **`Display for CacheBucket`** exposes the directory names (`wheels-v6`, `sdists-v9`, …) publicly even though `to_str()` is private — no API changes needed in `uv-cache`.\n- The **total in stats** may differ slightly from `cache size` because `cache size` walks the root recursively (including the `.lock` file), while stats only sums the 11 known buckets.",
